mitche: That is the 5 minute overview of Bergen
One point: If opener bids 3 of the agreed Major after a Bergen raise, it shows a minimum opener, not good enough to 
invite game.  
After a 3@C Bergen raise, I play that 3@D conventionally asks responder to show an outside control (A/K) and is Game Forcing.  
Some pairs play that 3@D asks responder to bid game on a maximum.  
So check with partner on follow ups to Bergen   3@C and 3@d.  
Bergen bids and follow ups are alertable.

